it's really weird how i had that weird dream about death the night before mckay passed on. i called corbin about it and told him about it, he had a dream like that too- except the exact opposite from mine. no one found out until a day later, apparently. it makes me really curious about death, but it doesn't make me any less scared. i wonder where people go after death, what they do. it's weird how we don't know at all. we think we know why the world turns or what the twinkling stars so far off really are, but why does that even matter. like what is life, you know? it's all just so surreal- physics, events, news, activities, improving yourself. where does life play a role in all of this? why is there suffering why is there pain. does what you do on this earth really matter in the end? what makes life actually unique? It's simply scary to think of what will happen after you stop breathing. what are you going to do after you die. what you will become. where do people go? do we just.. stop? everyone dies. but what does that mean? it's unfortunate that these age old questions still and will not be answered until the human experiences the phenomena. Five hundrend twenty five thousand six hundred minutes Five hundrend twenty five thousand moments so dear Five hundrend twenty five thousand six hundred minutes How do you measure, measure a year In daylight, sunsets, in midnights, in cups of coffee, In inches, in miles in laughter in strive, In Five hundrend twenty five thousand six hundred minutes How do you measure the life of a woman or a man? In truths that she learned Or in times that he cried In bridges he burned Or the way that he died --
